Middle East: The "Smart City" Sovereignty Report
Scenario: NEOM or a similar "Smart City" in Saudi Arabia is implementing a city-wide Biometric Identity System.
The Innovation: You are auditing the Sovereignty of the Human Identity.

Title: NEOM-Sovereign Identity: Auditing Biometric Resilience in Vision 2030 Smart Cities

Specialist: Melissa Rachel Wozney

The Issue: A city-wide facial recognition and biometric system creates a "Single Point of Failure" for 1 million citizens' identities.

Technical Audit: Mapping the biometric database to Saudi Aramco SACS-002 and NESA physical security standards.

Unique Solution: Proposed a Decentralized Identity (DID) framework where citizens "own" their biometric keys on a private blockchain, preventing a centralized database hack.
